# Handoff docs on task completion

When you **finish a Builder task** (code shipped, build green, commit/push done or Isaac confirmed complete):

1. Read `docs/handoff/HANDOFF-UPDATE.md`.
2. Update **`docs/handoff/CURRENT-STATE.md`** at minimum (`last updated` date, feature bullets, recent commits).
3. Update other handoff files from that checklist when the task touched product scope, routes, SQL, or workflow.
4. In your final reply, include **Handoff updated:** with the file paths you changed.

Skip only if the turn was Q&A/review with no repo changes, or Isaac said not to update.

Do not add secrets to handoff files.
